{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1521,"text":"Someday, we may have robots\nas smart as people,"},{"time":5989,"text":"artificial intelligence, AI."},{"time":8487,"text":"How could that happen?"},{"time":10812,"text":"One route is that we'll just keep\naccumulating better software,"},{"time":14020,"text":"like we've been doing for 70 years."},{"time":16543,"text":"At past rates of progress,\nthat may take centuries."},{"time":20138,"text":"Some say it'll happen a lot faster"},{"time":22512,"text":"as we discover grand new\npowerful theories of intelligence."},{"time":26407,"text":"I'm skeptical."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28608,"text":"But a third scenario"},{"time":31693,"text":"is what I'm going to talk about today."},{"time":33544,"text":"The idea is to port the software\nfrom the human brain."},{"time":36972,"text":"To do this, we're going to need\nthree technologies to be good enough,"},{"time":40297,"text":"and none of them are there yet."},{"time":42417,"text":"First, we're going to need\nlots of cheap, fast, parallel computers."},{"time":48855,"text":"Second, we're going to need\nto scan individual human brains"},{"time":53086,"text":"in fine spatial and chemical detail,"},{"time":55348,"text":"to see exactly what cells are where,\nconnected to what, of what type."},{"time":59400,"text":"And third, we're going to need\ncomputer models"},{"time":63780,"text":"of how each kind of brain cell works --"},{"time":67002,"text":"taking input signals,\nchanging interval state"},{"time":69606,"text":"and sending output signals."},{"time":70924,"text":"If we have good enough models\nof all the kinds of brain cells"},{"time":74766,"text":"and a good enough model of the brain,"},{"time":76553,"text":"we can put it together to make\na good enough model of an entire brain,"},{"time":80011,"text":"and that model would have the same\ninput-output behavior as the original."},{"time":84038,"text":"So if you talk to it, it might talk back."},{"time":86547,"text":"If you ask it to do things,\nit might do them."},{"time":88668,"text":"And if we could do that,\neverything would change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91514,"text":"People have been talking\nabout this idea for decades,"},{"time":94106,"text":"under the name of \"uploads.\""},{"time":95919,"text":"I'm going to call them \"ems.\""},{"time":98355,"text":"When they talk about it, they say,"},{"time":100983,"text":"\"Is this even possible?"},{"time":102838,"text":"If you made one, would it be conscious?\nOr is it just an empty machine?"},{"time":106213,"text":"If you made one of me,\nis that me or someone else?\""},{"time":109036,"text":"These are all fascinating questions\nthat I'm going to ignore ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112162,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":115041,"text":"because I see a neglected question:"},{"time":117154,"text":"What would actually happen?"},{"time":120440,"text":"I became obsessed with this question."},{"time":123993,"text":"I spent four years trying to analyze it,"},{"time":126970,"text":"using standard academic tools,\nto guess what would happen,"},{"time":130541,"text":"and I'm here to tell you what I found."},{"time":132928,"text":"But be warned --"},{"time":134722,"text":"I'm not offering inspiration,\nI'm offering analysis."},{"time":138153,"text":"I see my job as telling you\nwhat's most likely to happen"},{"time":140971,"text":"if we did the least to avoid it."},{"time":144132,"text":"If you aren't at least a bit disturbed\nby something I tell you here,"},{"time":147458,"text":"you're just not paying attention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149076,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":150451,"text":"OK, the first thing I can tell you"},{"time":153071,"text":"is that ems spend most\nof their life in virtual reality."},{"time":156819,"text":"This is what you might look like\nif you were using virtual reality."},{"time":162074,"text":"And this is what you might see:"},{"time":165244,"text":"sunlight glinting off of water,\nyou might hear gulls flying above,"},{"time":168864,"text":"you might even feel the wind\non your cheeks or smell seawater,"},{"time":171919,"text":"with advanced hardware."},{"time":174082,"text":"Now, if you were to spend\na lot of time here,"},{"time":176203,"text":"you might want a dashboard"},{"time":177493,"text":"where you could do things like\nmake a phone call,"},{"time":180011,"text":"move to a new virtual world,"},{"time":181585,"text":"check your bank account."}]},{"cues":[{"time":183960,"text":"Now, while this is what\nyou would look like in virtual reality,"},{"time":187641,"text":"this is what an em\nwould look like in virtual reality."},{"time":190793,"text":"It's computer hardware\nsitting in a server rack somewhere."},{"time":193573,"text":"But still, it could see\nand experience the same thing."},{"time":197282,"text":"But some things are different for ems."},{"time":199690,"text":"First, while you'll probably always notice\nthat virtual reality isn't entirely real,"},{"time":204500,"text":"to an em, it can feel as real to them\nas this room feels to you now"},{"time":207778,"text":"or as anything ever feels."},{"time":209440,"text":"And ems also have\nsome more action possibilities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":212389,"text":"For example, your mind just always\nruns at the same speed,"},{"time":215129,"text":"but an em can add more or less\ncomputer hardware to run faster or slower,"},{"time":218994,"text":"and therefore, if the world around them\nseems to be going too fast,"},{"time":222706,"text":"they can just speed up their mind,"},{"time":224349,"text":"and the world around them\nwould seem to slow down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":226723,"text":"In addition, an em can make\na copy of itself at that moment."},{"time":232120,"text":"This copy would remember\neverything the same,"},{"time":234241,"text":"and if it starts out with the same speed,\nlooking at the same speed,"},{"time":237581,"text":"it might even need to be told,\n\"You are the copy.\""},{"time":240779,"text":"And em could make archive copies,"},{"time":242376,"text":"and with enough archives,"},{"time":244224,"text":"an em can be immortal --"},{"time":246320,"text":"in principle, though not\nusually in practice."},{"time":249411,"text":"And an em can move its brain,\nthe computer that represents its brain,"},{"time":252967,"text":"from one physical location to another."},{"time":256037,"text":"Ems can actually move around the world\nat the speed of light,"},{"time":259379,"text":"and by moving to a new location,"},{"time":260935,"text":"they can interact more quickly\nwith ems near that new location."}]},{"cues":[{"time":264223,"text":"So far, I've been talking about\nwhat ems can do."},{"time":269227,"text":"What do ems choose to do?"},{"time":272405,"text":"To understand that, we'll need\nto understand three key facts."},{"time":276096,"text":"First, ems by definition do what\nthe human they emulate would do"},{"time":282271,"text":"in the same situation."},{"time":284305,"text":"So their lives and behavior\nare very human."},{"time":286972,"text":"They're mainly different because\nthey're living in a different world."},{"time":290293,"text":"Second, ems need\nreal resources to survive."},{"time":293615,"text":"You need food and shelter or you'll die."},{"time":297302,"text":"Also, ems need computer hardware,\nenergy, cooling, or they can't exist."},{"time":301636,"text":"For every subjective minute\nthat an em experiences,"},{"time":304235,"text":"someone, usually that em,\nhad to work to pay for it."},{"time":308136,"text":"Third, ems are poor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309850,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":311715,"text":"The em population can grow\nquicker than the em economy,"},{"time":314374,"text":"so that means wages fall down\nto em subsistence levels."},{"time":317733,"text":"That means ems have to be working\nmost of the time."},{"time":320361,"text":"So that means\nthis is what ems usually see:"},{"time":323684,"text":"beautiful and luxurious, but desks --"},{"time":326256,"text":"they're working most of the time."},{"time":328283,"text":"Now, a subsistence wage scenario,\nyou might think, is exotic and strange,"},{"time":332276,"text":"but it's actually the usual case\nin human history,"},{"time":334641,"text":"and it's how pretty much\nall wild animals have ever lived,"},{"time":337379,"text":"so we know what humans do\nin this situation."},{"time":339679,"text":"Humans basically do\nwhat it takes to survive,"},{"time":342633,"text":"and this is what lets me say\nso much about the em world."},{"time":346752,"text":"When creatures are rich, like you,"},{"time":349165,"text":"you have to know a lot\nabout what they want"},{"time":351212,"text":"to figure out what they do."},{"time":352577,"text":"When creatures are poor,"},{"time":353771,"text":"you know that they mostly do\nwhat it takes to survive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":356776,"text":"So we've been talking about the em world\nfrom the point of view of the ems --"},{"time":360424,"text":"now, let's step back\nand look at their whole world."},{"time":362963,"text":"First, the em world grows\nmuch faster than ours,"},{"time":366067,"text":"roughly a hundred times faster."},{"time":368555,"text":"So the amount of change\nwe would experience in a century or two,"},{"time":371742,"text":"they would experience in a year or two."},{"time":373624,"text":"And I'm not really willing to project\nthis age much beyond that,"},{"time":376686,"text":"because plausibly by then something else\nwill happen, I don't know what."},{"time":380147,"text":"Second, the typical emulation\nruns even faster,"},{"time":382529,"text":"roughly a thousand times human speed."},{"time":385316,"text":"So for them, they experience\nthousands of years in this year or two,"},{"time":390680,"text":"and for them, the world around them\nis actually changing more slowly"},{"time":393896,"text":"than your world seems to change for you."},{"time":396277,"text":"Third, ems are crammed together\nin a small number of very dense cities."},{"time":400785,"text":"This is not only how they see\nthemselves in virtual reality,"},{"time":404275,"text":"it's also how they actually are\nphysically crammed together."},{"time":407474,"text":"So at em speeds, physical travel\nfeels really painfully slow,"},{"time":411384,"text":"so most em cities are self-sufficient,"},{"time":413730,"text":"most war is cyber war,"},{"time":415504,"text":"and most of the rest of the earth\naway from the em cities"},{"time":418219,"text":"is left to the humans, because the ems\nreally aren't that interested in it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":422252,"text":"Speaking of humans,"},{"time":423784,"text":"you were wanting to hear about that."},{"time":425592,"text":"Humans must retire, at once, for good."},{"time":430887,"text":"They just can't compete."},{"time":432918,"text":"Now, humans start out owning\nall of the capital in this world."},{"time":436014,"text":"The economy grows very fast,\ntheir wealth grows very fast."},{"time":438907,"text":"Humans get rich, collectively."},{"time":442228,"text":"As you may know, most humans today\ndon't actually own that much"},{"time":445491,"text":"besides their ability to work,"},{"time":447356,"text":"so between now and then,\nthey need to acquire sufficient assets,"},{"time":450928,"text":"insurance or sharing arrangements,"},{"time":452785,"text":"or they may starve."},{"time":454270,"text":"I highly recommend avoiding this outcome."}]},{"cues":[{"time":456309,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":458465,"text":"Now, you might wonder,"},{"time":459712,"text":"why would ems let humans exist?"},{"time":461214,"text":"Why not kill them, take their stuff?"},{"time":463701,"text":"But notice we have many\nunproductive retirees around us today,"},{"time":466802,"text":"and we don't kill them\nand take their stuff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":468931,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":470589,"text":"In part, that's because it would disrupt\nthe institutions we share with them."},{"time":475524,"text":"Other groups would wonder who's next,"},{"time":477664,"text":"so plausibly, ems may well let humans\nretire in peace during the age of em."},{"time":482414,"text":"You should worry more that\nthe age of em only lasts a year or two"},{"time":485487,"text":"and you don't know what happens next."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489207,"text":"Ems are very much like humans,"},{"time":491597,"text":"but they are not like the typical human."},{"time":494438,"text":"The typical em is a copy\nof the few hundred most productive humans."},{"time":501329,"text":"So in fact, they are as elite,\ncompared to the typical human,"},{"time":504933,"text":"as the typical billionaire,\nNobel Prize winner,"},{"time":507219,"text":"Olympic gold medalist, head of state."},{"time":510527,"text":"Ems look on humans\nperhaps with nostalgia and gratitude,"},{"time":514853,"text":"but not so much respect,"},{"time":516385,"text":"which is, if you think about it,\nhow you think about your ancestors."},{"time":519604,"text":"We know many things about how humans\ndiffer in terms of productivity."},{"time":522895,"text":"We can just use those\nto predict features of ems --"},{"time":525338,"text":"for example, they tend to be smart,\nconscientious, hard-working,"},{"time":528458,"text":"married, religious, middle-aged."},{"time":530461,"text":"These are features of ems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":532097,"text":"Em world also contains enormous variety."},{"time":534710,"text":"Not only does it continue on with most\nof the kinds of variety that humans do,"},{"time":538402,"text":"including variety of industry\nand profession,"},{"time":540821,"text":"they also have many new kinds of variety,"},{"time":543007,"text":"and one of the most important\nis mind speed."},{"time":545712,"text":"Ems can plausibly go from human speed"},{"time":549570,"text":"up to a million times\nfaster than human speed,"},{"time":552474,"text":"and down to a billion times\nslower than human speed."},{"time":556226,"text":"Faster ems tend to have\nmarkers of high status."},{"time":559016,"text":"They embody more wealth.\nThey win arguments."},{"time":561200,"text":"They sit at premium locations."},{"time":562887,"text":"Slower ems are mostly retirees,"},{"time":564731,"text":"and they are like the ghosts\nof our literature."},{"time":567005,"text":"If you recall, ghosts are all around us --"},{"time":569070,"text":"you can interact with them\nif you pay the price."},{"time":571364,"text":"But they don't know much,\nthey can't influence much,"},{"time":573817,"text":"and they're obsessed with the past,\nso what's the point?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":576539,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":577714,"text":"Ems also have more variety\nin the structure of their lives."},{"time":580695,"text":"This is your life: you start\nand you end, really simple."},{"time":583401,"text":"This is the life of an em,"},{"time":585038,"text":"who every day splits off\nsome short-term copies"},{"time":587355,"text":"to do short-term tasks and then end."},{"time":589337,"text":"We'll talk more about\nthose short term versions in a moment,"},{"time":593488,"text":"but they are much more efficient"},{"time":595122,"text":"because they don't have to rest\nfor the next day."},{"time":597511,"text":"This em is more opportunistic."},{"time":599043,"text":"They make more copies of themselves\nwhen there's more demand for that."},{"time":602354,"text":"They don't know which way\nthe future's going."}]},{"cues":[{"time":604475,"text":"This is an em designer,"},{"time":605798,"text":"who conceives of a large system"},{"time":607424,"text":"and then breaks recursively into copies\nwho elaborate that,"},{"time":610933,"text":"so ems can implement\nlarger, more coherent designs."},{"time":614369,"text":"This an emulation plumber"},{"time":615751,"text":"who remembers that every day,\nfor the last 20 years,"},{"time":618220,"text":"they only ever worked\ntwo hours a day, a life of leisure."},{"time":621025,"text":"But what really happened is,\nevery day they had a thousand copies,"},{"time":624146,"text":"each of whom did a two-hour plumbing job,"},{"time":626123,"text":"and only one of them\nwent on to the next day."},{"time":628312,"text":"Objectively, they're working\nwell over 99 percent of the time."},{"time":631335,"text":"Subjectively, they remember\na life of leisure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":633549,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":634581,"text":"This, again, is you.\nYou start and you end."},{"time":636693,"text":"This could be you\nif at the start of party,"},{"time":638829,"text":"you took a drug that meant\nyou would not remember that party"},{"time":641664,"text":"ever after that day."},{"time":643306,"text":"Some people do this, I'm told."},{"time":645670,"text":"Toward the end of the party,"},{"time":647329,"text":"will you say to yourself,\n\"I'm about to die, this is terrible."},{"time":650279,"text":"That person tomorrow isn't me,\nbecause they won't remember what I do.\""},{"time":653606,"text":"Or you could say, \"I will go on tomorrow.\nI just won't remember what I did.\""},{"time":657591,"text":"This is an em who splits off\na short-term copy"},{"time":660044,"text":"to do a short-term task and then end."},{"time":661932,"text":"They have the same two\nattitude possibilities."},{"time":664162,"text":"They can say, \"I'm a new short-term\ncreature with a short life. I hate this.\""},{"time":667865,"text":"Or \"I'm a part of a larger creature\nwho won't remember this part.\""},{"time":671023,"text":"I predict they'll have\nthat second attitude,"},{"time":673165,"text":"not because it's philosophically correct,\nbut because it helps them get along."}]},{"cues":[{"time":676865,"text":"Today, if the president says\nwe must invade Iraq,"},{"time":679217,"text":"and you say, \"Why?\""},{"time":680392,"text":"and they say, \"State secret,\""},{"time":681798,"text":"you're not sure if you can trust them,"},{"time":683672,"text":"but for ems, a copy of the president\nand a copy of you can go inside a safe,"},{"time":687312,"text":"explain all their secret reasons,"},{"time":688990,"text":"and then one bit comes out\nfrom your copy to yourself,"},{"time":691545,"text":"telling you if you were convinced."},{"time":693425,"text":"So now you can know\nthere is a good reason."}]},{"cues":[{"time":695976,"text":"I know you guys are all eager\nto evaluate this world."},{"time":698545,"text":"You're eager to decide\nif you love it or hate it."},{"time":700903,"text":"But think: your ancestors\nfrom thousands of years ago"},{"time":703470,"text":"would have loved or hated your world"},{"time":705247,"text":"based on the first few things\nthey heard about it,"},{"time":707692,"text":"because your world\nis really just weird."},{"time":709579,"text":"So before judging a strange future world,\nyou should really learn a lot about it,"},{"time":713417,"text":"maybe read a whole book about it,"},{"time":715031,"text":"and then, if you don't like it,\nwork to change it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":717409,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":718452,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}